    "In addition, when the IoU-T was set to 0.5, 0.3 and 0.1, the mAPs of the Faster R-CNN model were 0.271, 0.423, and 0.508, respectively, while the mAPs of the RetinaNet model were 0.506, 0.632, and 0.678, respectively.",
    "More details about the AP of each abnormality determined by the two models are shown in Supplementary Table 5.",
